      "blocks": {
        "heading_im6WTc": {
          "type": "heading",
          "name": "How To Take Care Of Platinum Jewelry ",
          "settings": {
            "text": "How To Take Care Of Platinum Jewelry",
            "heading_level": "h2",
            "heading_id": "takecare",
            "alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "richtext_keRqLf": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Although platinum is one of the most durable metals, there can be scratches over time with use. These small scratches are sometimes loved by people as they cause a matte finish called patina. If you want to make your jewelry look brand new, some really quick remedies can bring back the original shine. </p><h3>1. Clean Platinum Jewelry At Home </h3><p>Use a very mild soap and mix it in a bowl of warm water. Soak your platinum jewelry in this bowl for approximately half an hour. Alternatively, you can also use a soft brush to gently remove dirt from beneath the stones, carefully without causing scratches. It’s recommended that if you’re storing your jewelry, keep it in a jewelry box and wipe the jewelry with a soft lint cloth. Lucira Jewelry’s packaging helps with maintaining this jewelry by letting the piece sit comfortably in a luxurious packaging designed to avoid any damage to the piece. </p><h3>2. Professional Maintenance </h3><p>Have your jeweler check your jewellery once every year. Check the prongs, the settings and the clasp to ensure that all stones are secured properly. Get the Jewelry deep cleaned every 1-2 years. </p><h3>3. Daily Wear Tips</h3><p>If you’re wearing your platinum jewelry daily, wear them last after dressing up, applying make up and wearing perfume. The ‘first off, last on’ helps with extra care without getting the Jewelry in contact with harsh chemicals or tangling with clothes. While doing heavy work, such as moving furniture or gardening, take off the jewelry such as platinum bracelets and platinum bangles to avoid scratches. </p>"
          }
        },
        "heading_A3eUcj": {
          "type": "heading",
          "name": "Why Choose Platinum Engagement Rings in India",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Why Choose Platinum Engagement Rings in India",
            "heading_level": "h3",
            "heading_id": "engagementrings",
            "alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "richtext_Lji6Dx": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Jewelry holds a deep cultural significance in India. When it comes to wedding shopping, gold used to be the obvious choice for Indian couples. However, this trend is changing as platinum gains popularity. Platinum’s natural white color enhances the beauty of diamonds that sit on the engagement ring. In India, <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/engagement-rings\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Engagement Rings\">engagement rings</a> are worn for a lifetime, signifying the love shared by the couple. Platinum is a promising metal to last a lifetime because it does not corrode, tarnish or get scratches easily. Platinum can rightfully be the symbol of a promise made to be together forever. Brides are choosing platinum engagement rings, not only because of their brilliance, but also because they are hypoallergenic, making them the perfect choice for sensitive skin. Platinum engagement rings are not just a style choice, but an investment in a rare metal while being a symbol of enduring love - best fitted for Indian couples.<br/><br/></p>"
          }
        }
      },
